what_failed: Regression (0.73x): Applied "pg_dimension_prefetch_star" optimization by creating separate CTEs for each filtered dimension table, converting implicit joins to explicit joins, and ensuring all required columns are preserved for downstream operations.
why_it_failed: All attempts failed because they over-relied on CTE materialization which creates optimization fences in PostgreSQL, preventing join order flexibility and predicate pushdown across CTE boundaries. Workers 1-5 essentially implemented the same strategy with minor variations: pre-filtering dimensions into CTEs then joining.
